1
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:08,039
Last week, my best friend came back
to life. The day before, he died.

2
00:00:08,040 --> 00:00:11,279
A few days before that, he emerges
as the most powerful member

3
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:13,199
of this tribe called the Angelics.

4
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,760
He acquires magical powers
they didn't even think was possible.

5
00:00:18,440 --> 00:00:22,039
People used to think he was mad.
They were wrong. He's special.

6
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:24,559
But him being special's
been a tumultuous time.

7
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:27,519
And that's not even half of it!
There's these dead people...

8
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:30,119
the Fades ... and they're
trying to come back to life,

9
00:00:30,120 --> 00:00:32,439
led by this dude called John,

10
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:35,679
who died in 1943 and has come back
to life by eating human flesh.

11
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:39,799
And now he's got a taste for it,
he just can't stop. Yeah, I know.

12
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:43,639
He tricked Paul into helping him rescue
this girl, Natalie, from the Angelics.

13
00:00:43,640 --> 00:00:48,839
And with her help, he's bringing a whole
army of dead people back into our town.

14
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:52,119
We've got to fight. Meanwhile,
the Angelics have their own plan.

15
00:00:52,120 --> 00:00:55,879
How?
By having one of our team on theirs.

16
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:58,439
Those of us in the middle of it ...
me, my history teacher,

17
00:00:58,440 --> 00:01:01,959
Paul's mum, Paul's sister, Paul's
girlfriend ... just stick out our chin,

18
00:01:01,960 --> 00:01:05,079
grin and try and pretend we
understand what's going on. Scary.

19
00:01:05,080 --> 00:01:08,559
Now, who's seen my Matrix box set?

20
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:13,279
I'm pretty sure I've worked out
who the Architect is a metaphor for.

21
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,719
Na-Nu, Na-Nu.

22
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:14,240
HE BREATHES LUSTFULLY

23
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:51,959
I've been waiting for over an hour!

24
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:54,439
'For those with
missing persons enquiries,

25
00:02:54,440 --> 00:02:58,839
'a crisis centre has been set up
at St Barnabus School.

26
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:04,200
'I repeat, a missing persons crisis
centre has been set up at the school.'

27
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,440
THEY LAUGH

28
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:23,639
I don't even know if he's all right
or if he should be here!

29
00:03:23,640 --> 00:03:25,919
The doctor didn't even
want to discharge you.

30
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:28,280
I am allowed to be worried.
He's fine. Watch this.

31
00:03:28,281 --> 00:03:29,719
Lord Of The Rings.

32
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:33,279
Why don't they just fly in and out of
Mordor on the back of a giant eagle?

33
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:36,479
Boom! They didn't want to
discharge him because he's too well.

34
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:38,959
That's ridiculous.
Mission Impossible 2.

35
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:40,900
Cruise finds a face
mask of the bodyguard

36
00:03:40,901 --> 00:03:42,839
without having seen or met him?

37
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,880
Likely(!) Kaboosh.

38
00:03:43,881 --> 00:03:47,439
Very few people actually come out of
a coma healthier. It's... odd.

39
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:51,839
My name is Dr Mac the Movie Doctor and
I pronounce a clear bill of health.

40
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:54,959
He's got a good recall
of basic facts. "Basic facts"?

41
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,679
The Matrix.

42
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,519
'This is Steve... '

43
00:03:58,520 --> 00:04:00,039
Where do I start? Direct hit.

44
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:03,199
Steve! Call me back!
Boom! Ssh! Boom!

45
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,440
Home run.

46
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,440
"Got well soon."

47
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,240
See what you've done there.

48
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:16,840
I'm OK, Mum. Good to have you home.

49
00:04:20,080 --> 00:04:22,680
Steve's still not
answering my calls.

50
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:30,279
Yeah, the school's going to be
a secondary location,

51
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,599
we're completely swamped
on missing persons.

52
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:35,919
Armstrong wouldn't know a suspect
if one bit him on the arse.

53
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:38,240
Look, Carol, I need to go, right?

54
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:45,199
Hello.

55
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,800
Hello.

56
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:01,440
KNOCK ON DOOR

57
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,439
We come in peace.

58
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:23,200
Oh, do you now?

59
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:26,240
That must be nice.

60
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,600
Sarah?!

61
00:05:40,720 --> 00:05:42,799
So why are you here? Paul's back.

62
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,840
What?

63
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,679
Back from the dead? Sarah?

64
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,079
Are you OK? So has he eaten, then?

65
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:52,599
No, He hasn't eaten.
He just... came back.

66
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,599
He closed an ascension point but..
The point's closed?

67
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,680
That's what happened, isn't it, eh?
Sarah...

68
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,599
Sarah's eaten, hasn't she?

69
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,999
Hasn't she? It was my idea.

70
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,639
At least we're trying
for a solution to this mess.

71
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:11,559
Sarah eats, she'll be reborn.

72
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:15,999
Immortal, just like him. The boy,
he came back. The boy's the answer!

73
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,238
The answer to what?

74
00:06:17,239 --> 00:06:18,480
People have died.

75
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:21,280
The boy's a joke.

76
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:25,319
We can beat them, we need to try.

77
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,519
With Sarah's help
we can start to fight back.

78
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:31,719
You're going to destroy her, Neil.
I'm not staying to watch.

79
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:34,079
RUMBLING AND RATTLING

80
00:06:34,080 --> 00:06:35,760
What's happening?

81
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,040
I don't know.

82
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,639
Must be him.

83
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,680
We've got to get
everyone out of here.

84
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,639
We've got two more.

85
00:07:06,640 --> 00:07:08,599
Good.

86
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,720
I love this.

87
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,280
I love you.

88
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:17,760
I've never been happier
than I am right now.

89
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,040
Thank you...

90
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:33,959
for what you did.

91
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:36,519
Tried and failed to save you?

92
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,159
Tried and failed to save me.

93
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:40,600
Pleasure. I came back from the dead.

94
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:45,999
What I am, who I am
has got to mean something.

95
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,760
It probably does.

96
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:54,919
MAC SPITS AND GARGLES

97
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,640
I was ready to ascend.

98
00:07:59,400 --> 00:08:02,119
I'd let everyone down,

99
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,000
and I was ready to leave this...

100
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,759
rock for ever.

101
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:11,639
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
so you came back to life.

102
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:12,960
But can you do this?

103
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,799
Can you though? No. Can you?

104
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,679
Well, then you're nothing to me.

105
00:08:19,680 --> 00:08:21,999
THEY LAUGH

106
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,480
Shut up!

107
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,919
Paul.

108
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:29,839
Don't tell anyone but there's
a real live girl in your room.

109
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:31,679
Are you wearing identical pyjamas?

110
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:34,480
Yeah, they were... they were
the only two I had clean.

111
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,360
Likely story.

112
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:43,640
So your mum was pretty clear
I should sleep in Anna's room.

113
00:08:44,760 --> 00:08:45,879
Yeah.

114
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:47,719
But I don't want to.

115
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,760
No?

116
00:08:52,280 --> 00:08:53,480
Oh. I get it.

117
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:57,719
Oh, don't mind me.
I'll just be quiet in the corner.

118
00:08:57,720 --> 00:09:01,040
You do anything you want to.
I won't listen or watch.

119
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:05,520
Sofa downstairs it is. Yeah.

120
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:08,999
Night.

121
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,240
Night.

122
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:20,439
You're not even scarred.

123
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,759
The doctor thinks me
a medical miracle.

124
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:24,800
The doctor thinks you're a freak.

125
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:29,080
You're my freak, though.

126
00:09:30,160 --> 00:09:31,240
Yeah.

127
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:43,759
You... Are you the man in charge?
How did you get in here?

128
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:46,359
You need to get everyone out
of town. It's not safe.

129
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:49,279
Full scale evacuation? Great!
You're just what I need(!)

130
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:52,359
You need to leave. Now. You're
going to die here. All of you!

131
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,999
If you don't get out,
you'll be arrested, understand?

132
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:59,839
Men with power. You think you can
scare me, you little, little man?

133
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,439
I'm actually average height.

134
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:04,359
Any news on Clement?

135
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,400
Nothing.

136
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:10,520
When do we add him to that?

137
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:13,159
What now?

138
00:10:13,160 --> 00:10:17,120
There's only one thing to do,
we've got to try and find Paul, eh?

139
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,080
Alice?

140
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,920
Rargh!

141
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:51,640
What's she?

142
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:55,080
The girlfriend?

143
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,119
Yeah.

144
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,160
Pretty.

145
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:03,959
Neil, what are you doing here?

146
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:07,040
BREATHES HEAVILY

147
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:12,800
'You were dead.'

148
00:11:12,801 --> 00:11:15,839
I know. And now you're back.

149
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,240
Alice thinks
that makes you important.

150
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:22,519
What do you think?

151
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:26,039
Oh, I think I should have a knife
at your throat right now.

152
00:11:26,040 --> 00:11:28,960
SHE SHIVERS

153
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:45,279
Why did you do it?

154
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:48,599
Why did you help him?
He promised he wouldn't hurt you.

155
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:50,520
And you believed him?

156
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:54,480
A murderer?
You were cutting Natalie up.

157
00:11:55,960 --> 00:11:57,680
You were torturing her.

158
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:02,679
He told me that's what the Angelics
had always done.

159
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:05,079
Suppressed, policed.

160
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,720
That's what I believed.

161
00:12:06,721 --> 00:12:08,360
What we did, we did for
the good of everyone.

162
00:12:09,960 --> 00:12:13,119
We thought they could be dangerous.
It turns out, we were right.

163
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:15,400
GROWLING

164
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:19,960
SHE PANTS

165
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:38,400
The past is a hole
and it's full of what-ifs.

166
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:41,599
And I live in the present.

167
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:45,519
You? Don't know where you live.

168
00:12:45,520 --> 00:12:46,879
You confuse me.

169
00:12:46,880 --> 00:12:50,320
GROWLING

170
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:53,080
HER NECK CRUNCHES

171
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:58,919
'One thing I do know... '

172
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:01,800
is that you are going to matter.

173
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,640
And when we find out why that is...

174
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:11,680
you'll have to pick a side.

175
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:20,120
Just make sure
you pick the right side, kid.

176
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:47,520
SHE BREATHES HUNGRILY

177
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:54,720
BLOOD DRIPS

178
00:14:05,280 --> 00:14:06,320
Hello, Sarah.

179
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,280
Welcome.

180
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:39,759
I can't...

181
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:40,880
You want to.

182
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:46,399
One time, during the war...

183
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:51,719
I was fighting alongside this NCO
called Richard... something.

184
00:14:51,720 --> 00:14:54,239
They brought a man
with his guts ripped out

185
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:56,040
into the hole that we were in.

186
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:01,679
Then someone shouted
for medical support...

187
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:04,319
and Richard raised his hand
in the air

188
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,600
"I'm a medic."

189
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:10,399
And then I watched him...

190
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:14,519
as he went and held
this man's guts together

191
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:16,560
and then watched him till he died.

192
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:20,639
And afterwards I said to him,

193
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:24,080
"Richard, I didn't know
that you were a medic."

194
00:15:26,320 --> 00:15:28,360
And he turned to me and he said...

195
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,920
"I'm not.

196
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:40,359
"I just wanted to know what
the insides of a man felt like."

197
00:15:40,360 --> 00:15:43,880
SHE PANTS

198
00:15:47,400 --> 00:15:49,600
Urges are OK.

199
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:54,360
They're human.

200
00:15:58,400 --> 00:15:59,519
Just eat.

201
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,680
And you'll be reborn.

202
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,840
Don't fight it, Sarah. We win.

203
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:17,399
SHE FEEDS NOISILY

204
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,440
Sarah?

205
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:24,960
Sarah! Oh...

206
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:32,200
WIND HOWLS

207
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,239
GLASS SHATTERS

208
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:54,800
Oh, shit. Mum?

209
00:17:04,200 --> 00:17:07,239
MUM!

210
00:17:07,240 --> 00:17:09,120
HE SNARLS

211
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:13,320
HE PANTS

212
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:21,920
Bad dream?

213
00:17:24,280 --> 00:17:25,360
Yeah.

214
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:30,800
I didn't wet the bed, though,
so that's a bonus.

215
00:17:37,040 --> 00:17:40,119
We're going to school. Are we?
They've set up a crisis centre.

216
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,799
Steve's not answering my calls.

217
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:45,119
I think he's missing and Mum says
she'll drive me but only if you come.

218
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:48,080
Paul, I'm not asking. I'm telling!

219
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:10,080
I don't know whether there's
enough people...

220
00:18:11,440 --> 00:18:14,599
Hi. Excuse me?
My name's Mark Etches.

221
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:16,159
I was told to report to you.

222
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:19,599
Not unless you're in need of help
and guidance you weren't.

223
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:23,039
Peter. Peter Tremlett. Doctor.

224
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:25,399
I'll be running
a counselling service.

225
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:30,079
Right. Well, thanks for coming in, Mark.
We're going to need everyone we can get.

226
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:33,519
Now, let's see if we can find someone
to show Mark around, all right?

227
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:35,480
OK.

228
00:18:38,640 --> 00:18:41,879
You really don't have to show me
everywhere, you know. I want to.

229
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:46,319
And just round here, we're starting up
an online database of missing persons.

230
00:18:46,320 --> 00:18:49,279
Steve? What you doing here?

231
00:18:49,280 --> 00:18:50,999
Didn't you know?

232
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,039
I'm dead civic-minded, sir.
I work with the elderly, too.

233
00:18:54,040 --> 00:18:55,959
Wiping their arses and everything.

234
00:18:55,960 --> 00:19:00,159
We've actually had a remarkably good
response to our request for volunteers.

235
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:02,160
I've got a clipboard and all.

236
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:17,159
Hi, hello. We're looking
for missing persons.

237
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:20,639
Who are you missing?
Steve. Steve McEwan. Steve?

238
00:19:20,640 --> 00:19:23,759
He's not missing. He's a volunteer.

239
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:28,040
Steve's a volunteer? He's helping
with the online databasing.

240
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:31,480
Anna, wait. Anna!

241
00:19:32,760 --> 00:19:34,920
I think I could be of more use here.

242
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:37,680
Yes, join me.

243
00:19:43,960 --> 00:19:45,559
Hello, stranger.

244
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:49,920
Oh... Hello, stranger still.

245
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:53,040
Surprised to see you here.

246
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,240
My housemate's mum has gone missing.

247
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:59,480
I'm... moral support.

248
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:02,879
Is your wife still missing?

249
00:20:02,880 --> 00:20:04,120
Um...

250
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,680
Pretty much officially dead.

251
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,159
Pink suits you.

252
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,359
SHE LAUGHS

253
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,479
What's so funny?

254
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:17,119
What? What's so funny?

255
00:20:17,120 --> 00:20:21,799
Sorry, who are you? Oh, Vicky,
this is... Dr Tremlett, right?

256
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:26,199
No, no, no, sorry.
I'm just kind of interested...

257
00:20:26,200 --> 00:20:30,679
in what's so funny right now, yeah?

258
00:20:30,680 --> 00:20:33,599
