524
00:44:14,840 --> 00:44:18,039
I'm here as a citizen,

525
00:44:18,040 --> 00:44:19,919
as a man,

526
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:21,640
as a father...

527
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:26,759
to tell you I think
you should leave town.

528
00:44:26,760 --> 00:44:30,959
We don't know what's happening,
we don't know how it's happening,

529
00:44:30,960 --> 00:44:35,559
and we have no idea how to stop it.
Not the murders,

530
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:38,600
the attacks, or the tremors.

531
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:44,080
We need to evacuate now.

532
00:44:47,000 --> 00:44:48,360
Now!

533
00:44:54,640 --> 00:44:57,320
SIRENS WAIL

534
00:45:06,360 --> 00:45:08,560
This can't be why I came back.

535
00:45:10,760 --> 00:45:12,079
No.

536
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:15,119
I killed Steve.

537
00:45:15,120 --> 00:45:17,400
And that... girl.

538
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:20,960
Natalie.

539
00:45:23,360 --> 00:45:25,919
They burnt up.

540
00:45:25,920 --> 00:45:29,759
But they were dead already, right?
I don't want to be a killer.

541
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:32,119
You don't have to be one.

542
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:38,039
Superman could crush Lois Lane after
an argument about the washing-up.

543
00:45:38,040 --> 00:45:42,160
He could melt the Daily Planet
after a bad day at the office.

544
00:45:43,680 --> 00:45:45,160
He doesn't.

545
00:45:46,240 --> 00:45:48,560
He uses his powers for good.

546
00:45:50,560 --> 00:45:52,080
That's all you need to do.

547
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:01,840
Got to go.

548
00:46:05,440 --> 00:46:09,200
SIRENS WAIL

549
00:46:15,960 --> 00:46:17,759
It's you and me, then.

550
00:46:17,760 --> 00:46:22,159
We start a clean up, Paul, now.
And identify them? How?

551
00:46:22,160 --> 00:46:26,959
I can't tell them apart from
ordinary people, can you?

552
00:46:26,960 --> 00:46:31,119
We don't even know how many of them
there are. Well, we'll find a way.

553
00:46:31,120 --> 00:46:33,920
A way that doesn't involve me
killing everyone?

554
00:46:36,240 --> 00:46:38,119
Look after him, won't you?

555
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:39,399
Paul?

556
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:42,200
I think he can look after himself.

557
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:47,479
Look after your mum.

558
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:49,960
That I will try to do.

559
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:54,879
Look after yourself.

560
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:56,599
You want me to look after me?

561
00:46:56,600 --> 00:46:58,920
Yeah.

562
00:47:02,720 --> 00:47:04,320
Give me your hands.

563
00:47:09,880 --> 00:47:11,519
You've got three seconds. OK.

564
00:47:11,520 --> 00:47:13,199
Three.

565
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:15,999
Two. One.

566
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:17,880
OK? OK.

567
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:25,360
Look after yourself, too.

568
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:28,920
Yeah.

569
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:31,520
You ready?

570
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,480
Probably not.

571
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:36,960
Come on.

572
00:47:45,280 --> 00:47:47,520
A 17-year-old boy, Neil.

573
00:47:49,040 --> 00:47:52,160
And if these powers have been
given to me for a reason, then...

574
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:56,679
maybe it's not to kill everyone.

575
00:47:56,680 --> 00:48:00,919
Maybe it's because I can see past
your shit and his shit.

576
00:48:00,920 --> 00:48:02,959
Is that the shit
that just saved your life?

577
00:48:02,960 --> 00:48:05,959
If all the world
needed was more death...

578
00:48:05,960 --> 00:48:09,839
then you'd have been given these powers.
If I had one-tenth of your powers,

579
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:12,719
I'd be giving you
such a fucking kicking.

580
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:15,679
I'm going to find a better plan.

581
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:17,199
Another way.

582
00:48:17,200 --> 00:48:19,799
Ascension is broken,
I'm going to put it right.

583
00:48:19,800 --> 00:48:21,839
Better? You think you can do better?

584
00:48:21,840 --> 00:48:24,100
You're signing a death
warrant for everyone here.

585
00:48:24,101 --> 00:48:26,359
There's going to be
reborns everywhere.

586
00:48:26,360 --> 00:48:27,880
DON'T WALK AWAY FROM ME!

587
00:48:45,560 --> 00:48:47,280
DOORBELL RINGS

588
00:49:14,800 --> 00:49:15,920
Hello.

589
00:49:20,160 --> 00:49:21,479
Hi.

590
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:23,000
Can I come in?

591
00:49:47,840 --> 00:49:49,439
You've got no time. No time.

592
00:49:49,440 --> 00:49:52,599
Dad, I have things here worth
thousands of pounds on eBay.

593
00:49:52,600 --> 00:49:54,680
I refuse to rush.

594
00:50:07,720 --> 00:50:09,160
Yeah. Why rush?

595
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:13,040
Tortoise always wins.

596
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:20,559
I'm here to take you with me, Mac.

597
00:50:20,560 --> 00:50:22,599
Where?

598
00:50:22,600 --> 00:50:25,839
Somewhere I can persuade Paul
to follow.

599
00:50:25,840 --> 00:50:28,159
You're taking me hostage?

600
00:50:28,160 --> 00:50:29,799
Yeah.

601
00:50:29,800 --> 00:50:32,479
That's about the most efficient
way of putting it.

602
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:34,119
Why?

603
00:50:34,120 --> 00:50:39,279
Because he's stronger than me
in every way...

604
00:50:39,280 --> 00:50:41,439
except one.

605
00:50:41,440 --> 00:50:43,879
He has people he cares about.

606
00:50:43,880 --> 00:50:46,399
I'm his weakness?

607
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:48,799
Yep.

608
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:52,359
And I intend to take
full advantage of that fact.

609
00:50:52,360 --> 00:50:54,679
MAC'S DAD: Come on, Mac. Hurry up.

610
00:50:54,680 --> 00:50:59,760
Don't make me hurt your dad, Mac,
because I am this close.

611
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:20,080
Get a move on.

612
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:24,360
Mac!

613
00:51:29,680 --> 00:51:31,240
Mac!

614
00:51:33,160 --> 00:51:34,559
Mac!

615
00:51:34,560 --> 00:51:37,679
Paul, kitchen.
Anna, get some clothes.

616
00:51:37,680 --> 00:51:39,239
Jay, call your mum.

617
00:51:39,240 --> 00:51:41,240
You've got five minutes.

618
00:51:42,520 --> 00:51:44,119
Paul.

619
00:51:44,120 --> 00:51:46,039
What I saw you do...

620
00:51:46,040 --> 00:51:47,760
Best to forget about that, Mum.

621
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:53,520
Sometimes, I'd sit outside your room
listening to you have nightmares.

622
00:51:55,720 --> 00:51:57,240
I'm scared.

623
00:51:59,240 --> 00:52:01,759
That's understandable.

624
00:52:01,760 --> 00:52:06,000
I don't know whether to be
scared for you or scared of you.

625
00:52:07,560 --> 00:52:10,440
I'm going to make you
proud of me, Mum.

626
00:52:12,840 --> 00:52:14,800
I hope so.

627
00:52:22,000 --> 00:52:23,880
I'm a teeny tiny bit claustrophobic,

628
00:52:23,881 --> 00:52:26,400
so if you could leave the light on...
Shut up.

629
00:53:09,720 --> 00:53:11,159
Can you knock?!

630
00:53:11,160 --> 00:53:14,799
Erm, where's that
stripy hoodie of yours?

631
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:19,160
Have you packed all the food?
We need to move quickly.

632
00:53:28,640 --> 00:53:30,760
DOG BARKS

633
00:53:51,680 --> 00:53:53,080
I'll kill you.

634
00:53:54,480 --> 00:53:55,960
Now!

635
00:53:57,040 --> 00:53:59,680
You make one move towards my family.

636
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:04,799
Jesus. That almost
sounded grown-up, then.

637
00:54:04,800 --> 00:54:07,519
That was very manly, very good.

638
00:54:07,520 --> 00:54:09,559
I meant...

639
00:54:09,560 --> 00:54:13,279
I mean it. You know,
it's interesting, isn't it?

640
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:15,239
When I kill,

641
00:54:15,240 --> 00:54:17,999
people can come back.

642
00:54:18,000 --> 00:54:21,079
But then when you kill,
people are wiped from existence.

643
00:54:21,080 --> 00:54:24,319
Yeah? Why's that interesting?

644
00:54:24,320 --> 00:54:27,560
Because I'm the one
people think is the monster.

645
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:33,399
And today, you killed the one
person I had left that I loved.

646
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:36,319
And I wanted you
to feel similar pain.

647
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:39,040
Me and you, we're the same.

648
00:54:41,000 --> 00:54:43,719
I'm the chosen one of my people.

649
00:54:43,720 --> 00:54:48,880
You're the chosen one of yours.
Nah, we're not alike.

650
00:54:52,880 --> 00:54:56,599
I will find a way...

651
00:54:56,600 --> 00:54:58,879
to hurt you.

652
00:54:58,880 --> 00:55:00,400
To kill you.

653
00:55:02,360 --> 00:55:06,359
I didn't come back to be a monster.

654
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:07,640
D'you hear me?

655
00:55:08,920 --> 00:55:11,200
I'll find a way to help you.

656
00:55:12,200 --> 00:55:15,039
Free you. No, good luck with that.

657
00:55:15,040 --> 00:55:17,840
You have been NOTHING
but helpful so far.

